  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ContinuousFunction<UD extends javax.measure.Quantity<UD>,UR extends javax.measure.Quantity<UR>>
    A set of domain values (X) mapped via some continuous function to a corresponding value in the range (Y).
    ContinuousFunctionDecorator<UD extends javax.measure.Quantity<UD>,UR extends javax.measure.Quantity<UR>>
    A partial implementation of a ContinuousFunction decorator, to reduce boilerplate for functions which are in some way mappings of other functions.
    DataProperties  
    Dimension<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>
    This object represents the dimension of a continuous function, as well as all values of the function in that dimension.
    Domain<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>  
    PeakShapeFunction
    An interface for describing a peak shape function which can be sampled over an effective area.
    PeakShapeFunctionFactory
    Factory for generating normalised PeakShapeFunctions at a given position, and of a given total intensity.
    Range<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>  
    SampledContinuousFunction<UD extends javax.measure.Quantity<UD>,UR extends javax.measure.Quantity<UR>>
    A partial-implementation of ContinuousFunction for sampled continua.
    SampledDimension<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>
    A dimension of the sample space of a sampled continuous function.
    SampledDomain<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>
    Implementations of this class must be immutable, though it is not guaranteed than an implementation of SampledContinuousFunction will return the same instance for each invocation of ContinuousFunction.domain().

    SampledRange<U extends javax.measure.Quantity<U>>
